        <!-- required for collection level; optional for lower levels -->
        <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">

            <head>Scope and Content Note</head>
            <p>The Hines mss., 1942-1996 consists of photograph albums, audio and video recordings,
                and other memorabilia relating to Hines' career. The photograph albums contain
                material relating to various opera balls in 1970s-1980s, the Marylawn concerts of
                the 1960s-1970s, career highlights, personal and publicity shots, and Hines's
                performance in <title render="italic">La Traviata.</title> The video recordings
                include an undated performance of <title render="italic">La Traviata,</title> and a
                television interview from Nov. 26, 1996. An audio cassette contains arias, popular,
                and inspirational songs. A poster advertising the 11th annual Jerome Hines Marylawn
                Concert completes the collection.</p>
        </scopecontent>

